meta.name: Cell Phone Microbiome Project
meta.description:
1. Fall 2023 BIO 327-01 Sample Sheet: The samples that were sequenced along with their average number of pick-ups and their category.

2. samplefile.xslx: The sample sheet I fed to the analysis software so it could categorize each sample.

3. otu_summary_table.txt: The number of observations (number of reads) for each sample.

4. taxononomy_table.txt: The taxonomy of each of the different OTUs in all of the samples.

5. OTU_table.txt: The number of reads for each OTU in each sample.

6. taxa.biom: A file that combines the OTU table and taxonomy table in a format that can be read by MicrobiomeDB, which we are using for our data analysis.

meta.name: "Astarte_NICUbiome_Processed_01262021"
meta.description: ""Contains 2995 samples from 267 premature infants. Any taxa and function that have a zero relative abundance in every sample of the table is filtered out. Additionally, one sample in the Functions table had a value of 0 for every feature, so it was removed. OTU Table and Metadata are included. ""

meta.name: "Astarte_NICUbiome_Filtered_01262021"
meta.description: ""Contains 2955 samples from 267 premature infants. Any taxon/function that is < 0.000001 (0.0001%) sum relative abundance across all samples as well as any taxon/function that is present in < 1% of all samples was filtered out. Non-bacterial taxa were removed from the OTU table. Any samples that now had an abundance of 0 for every feature due to filtering were removed, and then relative abundances in both tables were renormalized. Finally, samples were removed from both tables if that sample had fewer than 100,000 aligned reads from MetaPhlAn2 annotation. Only samples that remained in both the functional and OTU table were retained in both. OTU Table and Metadata are included. ""

meta.name: "Lactobacillus for Cancer Therapy-ITS-1"
meta.description: "Table Even Depth Taxa - ITS sequences"

meta.summary: "Microbiome: Bacteriome & Mycobiome of rat fecal samples related to cancer, chemotherapy and no-drug alternative additive natural medicine-16S-Table3"
meta.name: "Lactobacillus for Cancer Therapy-16S-3"
meta.description:
"Table Bacteriome Taxa - 16S sequences in relation with cancer and bio-therapy 

Here, we tackle the problem linked to chemotherapy as a main remedy for cancer, emphasizing on its severe impact on the immune system and therefore on the urgent need for new additive biomedical products in cancer treatment. 

The experiment was conducted using a rat model of chemotherapy (cyclophosphamide CTX), which was shown to have a depleted immune system. In this new study, we showed the complete rat
microbiota, i.e. the collection of fungal and bacterial microorganisms, which resides in the rat intestinal gut flora in relation with chemotherapy for cancer and new lactobacillus probiotic
pharmacology. See 16S & ITS sequences.

We report about several bacterial and fungal phyla, classes, orders, families, genera and species associated with chemotherapy and immune injury. We also report about specific bacterial and fungal strains that are specifically regulated by addition of Lactobacillus (three doses) to CTX chemo. 

We demonstrate that a new natural pharmacological agent (3L bioproduct, 3 lactobacilli) is extremely efficient in re-establishing a strong sustainable beneficial healthy gut flora, which is a prerequisite not only for boosting metabolic pathways and immune responses, but also for recovering good health conditions.

Our work calls for a need to shift from chemotherapy to chemotherapy + lactobacillus treatment in patients suffering a cancer disease, and proposes a new probiotic formulation to be explored by pharmaceutical industry in prevention of health condition loss by alteration of the general immune system.

See Frontiers in Pharmacology
Lactobacillus on recovering of immune-damage by chemoradiotherapy (cancer treatment)
Shousong Yuea, Zhenzhong Zhangb, Fei Biana, Yan Zhanga, Gao Chena, Jun Lib and Jean-François Picimbonac1

aShandong Academy of Agricultural Sciences, Jinan, China
bShandong First Medical University & Shandong Academy of Medical Sciences, Jinan, China
cQilu University of Technology, Jinan, China
jfpicimbon@gmail.com

Short title Improving cancer treatment by natural bioproduct (Frontiers)"

meta.name: HBO acute stress
meta.description: A. fumigatus (CEA10) spores (1E+04) were point inoculated on GMM and incubated at 37C for 36 hours. Plates were then incubated in normobaric air or hyperbaric oxygen (3.5ATA or 36.7 psi) for 2 hours. RNA was isolated and 3' end sequencing was done. Data was analyzed with Galaxy using HiSAt2 - HtSeq - DrSeq2 pipeline.

meta.name: RNA seq Normoxia
meta.description: A. fumigatus conidia were grown (1E+04) for 36 hours in GMM and were subjected to normoxia or HBO (3.5ATA, 36.7psi) for 2 hours at RT. RNA was isolated from whole colonies on plate and 3' polyA 70bp single end sequencing was performed at Dartmouth Core.
